Package: pdfgrep
Version: 2.0.1-1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Christoph Egger <christoph@debian.org>
Installed-Size: 96
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.14), libgcc1 (>= 1:3.0), libgcrypt20 (>= 1.7.0), libpcre3, libpoppler-cpp0v5 (>= 0.46.0), libstdc++6 (>= 5.2)
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: http://pdfgrep.org
Description: search in pdf files for strings matching a regular expression
 Pdfgrep is a tool to search text in PDF files. It works similar to
 `grep'.
 .
 Features:
  - search for regular expressions.
  - support for some important grep options, including:
    + filename output.
    + page number output.
    + optional case insensitivity.
    + count occurrences.
  - and the most important feature: color output!
